### 📌 @Component — When to Use

Use `@Component` when your class doesn't clearly belong to any layer:

```java
// Utility class — not service, not repo, not controller
@Component
public class EmailValidator {

    public boolean isValid(String email) {
        return email.contains("@");
    }
}

// Inject anywhere
@Service
public class StudentService {

    @Autowired
    private EmailValidator emailValidator;   // injected automatically
}
```

