### 📌 Bean Naming with Stereotype Annotations

```java
// Default bean name = class name with lowercase first letter
@Service
public class StudentService { }
// bean id = "studentService"

// Custom name
@Service("stuService")
public class StudentService { }
// bean id = "stuService"

// Fetch by name
StudentService s = (StudentService) ctx.getBean("studentService");

// Fetch by type (cleaner)
StudentService s = ctx.getBean(StudentService.class);
```

